                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#62v">ff. 62v</locus>: Condemnation for those who steal the book.<quote xml:lang="gez"> f. 62v: ለዘሰረቃ፡ ወለዘፈሐቋ፡ በስልጣነ፡ ኣብ፡ ወወ[ል]ድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is crudely written in red (crimson) pen and mentions Gabra Krǝstos.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letter added in a secondary hand at the end of the line: fol. 20v.&#xD;
- Omitted letter added interlineally, possibly in the main hand: fol. 58v.&#xD;
- Correction written in a secondary hand: fol. 49v.&#xD;
- Erasure marked with thin black lines: fol. 23r.&#xD;
- Several names are crudely written in a secondary hand over erased names in the supplication formulas: Gabra Krǝstos (fols. 38v, 39r, 62r) and his maid Walatta Māryām (fols. 38v, 62r).&#xD;
- Crude drawings in black pen of St Michael, St Gabriel, the Virgin and her Child on fols. 1r and 63r.&#xD;
- Scribbles: e.g., fols. 1r, 1v, 2r.&#xD;
- Doodles in pencil: fols. 4v, 6v, 20r, 26v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
